2.01	Scapigliatura	Scapigliatura	Scapigliatura is the name of the artistic movement which developed in Italy after the period known as Risorgimento, (1815–1871, which led to the unification of Italy and the modern Italian state). Scapigliatura is the Italian equivalent of the French bohème and Scapigliati (literally "dishevelled", "unkempt") the name given to this group of artists which included poets and writers, musicians, painters and sculptors.	
